headline: Nvidia stock needs 'perfect' Q2: How to trade a post-earnings dip
summary: As investors wait for Nvidia's (NVDA) earnings report, Slatestone Wealth chief market strategist Kenny Polcari, who is also the host of Yahoo Finance's Trader Talk podcast, outlines his strategy for navigating a post-earnings dip in the artificial intelligence (AI) chipmaker stock. The strategist discusses trading other AI names like AMD (AMD), Palantir (PLTR), and Intel (INTC), as well as hyperscalers like Amazon (AMZN) and Meta (META) in the aftermath of Nvidia's earnings print. Tune in to Yahoo Finance on Wednesday, Aug. 27 at 4:15 p.m. for special coverage of Nvidia's quarterly results, followed by an exclusive interview with Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang at 6:40 p.m. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.

headline: Nvidia Has the Power to Move Markets. Watch These Sectors.
summary: It’s rare that a single company has the potential to move markets but Nvidia's earnings report has that power and will be key for multiple sectors.  The artificial-intelligence trade is the driver behind not just chip companies but also utilities, energy, cloud-computing and software stocks.  “Nvidia is the ultimate bellwether for the AI story and investors look to this company every quarter for reassurance that the AI story is still intact,” said Clark Bellin, president of wealth manager Bellwether Wealth.
